dataObject.content: YouTube is making clear there will be no "birtherism" on its platform during this year’s U.S. presidential election – a belated response to a type of conspiracy theory more prevalent in the 2012 race.

annotationData.content: {"category":{"label":"Biased"},"rationale":"Not allowing somebody to use their free speech to express their beliefs is biased against their way of thinking, it doesn't matter if they are right or wrong. People reading and watching on YouTube can decide for themselves what they want to believe. Banning anything right-wing is biased against the right wing, whether they be right or wrong. Sometimes conspiracy theories are true."}

{"category":{"label":"Biased"},"rationale":"biased because it attributes a judgment to youtube's attitude when it says it's ''a belated response'' therefore, if there is judgment, there is no impartiality."}
